        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/25/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 15:35:12</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=774"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=774')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=33434&TOPIC_ID=4489&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=The+litmus+for+class+balance&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Pepole want wants going to get them thier goals the fastest quickest way.</P><P>The reason necros are not welcome is because we take too long to do any good (dots) or have probs that make us unsafe (pets).</P><P>Someday Verant will realise that class abilities must be shared amongst classes in order for there to be balance...</P><P>Wizzies = nuke kings but mages = good nukers also</P><P>Druids = damage shields/snare/port - but all other classes can fill in here</P><P>Shammans = buff/slow - enchanters can do this to some degree</P><P>Enchanters = mezz kings/mana kings - bards can do this a bit but do not = enchanters.</P><P>Mages = pets and nukeage - necros are not close on the pets and wizards outnuke - but not by much</P><P>Cleric = healers - they don't do much else - this is sad because it makes them guard the role of healing so jealously... no other class could ever hope to make up for a cleric healing.  It would take an entire group of shamman/druids to equal the healing power of just 1 cleric.</P><P>War/Monk/Rouge/Ranger/Paladin/Shadownight - these classes all can hit - some better than others - some get hit alot worse than others... but they all have balances/tradeoffs that make any choice a good choice depending on your playstyle.  Yes you can substiute a pally for a war to a limited extent.</P><P>So what does that leave us with?</P><P>The necro... who does alot of things on his own... can regen HIS mana faster than anything in the game... yet has little that he can cast in the end game to justify this enormous mana gain.</P><P>I love my necro in a group... I love my necro solo - but on a raid it's 'twitch the cleric' blah...</P><P>Mabey if they gave another class complete heal they could give clerics some type of neato effect... and spread around the balance a bit to allow all the classes to contribute...</P><P>I will never understand Verant's logic in that making a 500dmg nuke chain castable by a necro is a bad thing when it's chain castable by a mage and druid and wizard and enchanter....</P><P>Why is a 300dmg lifetap on a lure line so imbalanced... if you can make lures high lvl why would this change the lifetap spell line in general.. wizards get lures and they don't have special bennifits to early spells..</P><P>I don't understand why letting a caster have a nuke that does mega damage without a huge taunt would be a bad thing.  </P><P>Here is my view on damage:</P><P>If a warrior can swing for 50 dmg a whack and gets usually 2-3 hits a round... that's 150 dmg a round.  The warrior can do this as long as clerics are around to heal him.</P><P>A wizard should (at high lvls) have spells that allow them to do 4000 dmg in a single cast - mabey with a 600 mana hit... why?  because they can do incredible damage... but they run out of mana quickly.</P><P>Now the only way this could work is if point for point the mob will agro the tank as much as the wizard... that doesn't seem to be how it works now... many spells I see put you at the top of the hate list no matter how mad the mob is at someone else... that's not just adding +100 hate or something ... that's saying hate = current max hate+100</P><P>That sucks.</P><P>If my rouge friend can double backstab every 10 secs for 400-500 dmg for no mana why can't I cast a spell that does 1200dmg in 10-12 secs for 400 mana...</P><P>ALSO... why is it cast times get longer on spells as you gain in lvls... </P><P>Cast times on spells should never be above 4-5secs... mabey a few that are longer but those spells should be huge spells that do everything but the kitchen sink.</P><P>Specilization should allow a caster to cast a spell with a count of cast time/4 round up on a success..</P><P>These are my ideas anyway...  I just don't get the high end caster game... tanks get faster and harder to hit and do godly damage.. while all casters sit there with limited mana (which there is no 'complete med' spell) and do what... 1200 dmg on the best wizzy nuke???  </P><P>Geesh... that just did 1200dmg to that mob with 15k hps... oh look he quad hits for 120... and look he summons... and look you have 1000 hps buffed... oh yes and look now that he is done eating you the tanks will do 12k dmg in about 20 secs...</P><P>(I have seen a warrior using the crit disc do 1500dmg in like 15 secs... so yes this is possible).</P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

